cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on object detection in crowded scenes. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel approach using two-stage detectors and human-shaped masks, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as R-CNN and Non-Maximum-Suppression (NMS), making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves the use of high-resolution images and fine-grained features, which could fall under cs.MM. Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of current object detection methods and proposes a new approach, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
